      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/nagaraja-cou1-vr-stiffness",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Construct stiffness QoI comparison — multi-lab N=11",
      "description": "FEA-predicted construct stiffness compared against N=11 physical specimens across two independent laboratories. Mean absolute percent error 4.7%; all specimens within the pre-specified 10% acceptance bound. E/uval ratio 1.41, below the 1.96 threshold. Multi-laboratory concordance strengthens confidence in experimental reference data."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/nagaraja-cou1-vr-yield",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Yield force and 40 mm displacement force QoI comparison",
      "description": "Yield force predictions fell within 7.2% of experimental means; force at 40 mm displacement within 8.9%. Both quantities satisfy the <10% acceptance criterion. E/uval values were 1.62 and 1.83 respectively, both below 1.96. The ensemble of three independent FEA implementations (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) showed inter-model spread of less than 3%, supporting numerical robustness."
    }
